According to the analyses, the comet is traveling on a so-called hyperbole railway, which leads it out of our system - and clearly of interstellar origin, as the International Astronomical Union (IAU) announced. She is also responsible for the naming and categorization of celestial bodies. In honor of its discoverer, the interstellar tail star, which had initially been listed under the catalog number C/2019 Q4, was designated 2I/Borisov, with the first part of the name indicating that it is the second interstellar object to have been discovered in our solar system.
