The Canadian Green Party leader holds a reusable cup in her hand in a photo. But now it came out: The cup was manipulated.
Ottawa/Canada - It has gone unnoticed for quite a long time - and finally noticed. Elizabeth May, the head of the Canadian Green Party, never held the reusable coffee cup with a metal straw in her hand. On the party's website, she was featured in a photo with this cup, in conversation with citizens. However, the photo had already been published before and also distributed to the media - and the cup was still a sniffy (cardboard) cup, as the Canadian National Post reported.
Greens leader has to answer for photo breakdown
