May was shocked and said on her blog that she knew nothing about this action. To emphasize this, she immediately posted the original: she, in conversation with citizens, a cup in hand. However, she said correctly was made of bamboo. She always has him with her. A spokeswoman for the party said it was only a matter of putting the party logo in the picture, and not about covering up anything. Only one snippet of the photo can be seen on the website.
May writes that she is sorry for the employee who did this. "I don't want to call him stupid, but there was nothing to hide," she told the Guardian, and asked herself something from her over-engaged team: "If they want to edit a picture again, could they not do something with my face, so that I look younger?"
